1
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:12,040
What a relief.

2
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:14,400
This time it really showed that

3
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,879
every cloud has a silver lining.

4
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,639
I believe our Feimanchi will definitely

5
00:01:18,639 --> 00:01:20,080
have a very bright future.

6
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:21,959
All right, Old Hu.

7
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:22,800
You just

8
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:23,720
focus on doing your job well.

9
00:01:24,040 --> 00:01:24,480
Okay.

10
00:01:25,440 --> 00:01:26,040
I have some things to do.

11
00:01:26,239 --> 00:01:26,720
I'll leave you to it.

12
00:01:26,839 --> 00:01:27,319
Okay.

13
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:39,839
CEO.

14
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:41,599
Are you busy?

15
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:42,680
Yes.

16
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:43,639
I have to keep an eye on things.

17
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:46,239
This feels really great.

18
00:01:47,160 --> 00:01:47,959
The storm has passed,

19
00:01:48,839 --> 00:01:49,879
and production can resume.

20
00:01:51,519 --> 00:01:52,000
Yeah.

21
00:01:52,559 --> 00:01:53,120
By the way,

22
00:01:53,959 --> 00:01:54,760
I forgot my phone.

23
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,279
Could I borrow your phone

24
00:01:56,279 --> 00:01:56,919
for a second?

25
00:01:58,959 --> 00:01:59,360
Sure.

26
00:02:00,160 --> 00:02:00,559
Thanks.

27
00:02:08,399 --> 00:02:09,399
What are you doing?

28
00:02:10,119 --> 00:02:10,440
What's wrong?

29
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,360
So many workers are watching.

30
00:02:32,639 --> 00:02:33,520
Don't you want the phone?

31
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:37,160
Here.

32
00:02:38,279 --> 00:02:39,000
Why are you running?

33
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:41,679
You're unbelievable.

34
00:02:42,360 --> 00:02:43,520
What if someone sees us?

35
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:44,880
So what if they do?

36
00:02:45,679 --> 00:02:46,880
I want them all to know

37
00:02:46,880 --> 00:02:47,800
that I'm pursuing you.

38
00:02:49,839 --> 00:02:50,600
I told you before,

39
00:02:50,839 --> 00:02:52,119
as for me, Gu Tiancheng,

40
00:02:52,399 --> 00:02:53,559
if I like someone, I have to show it.

41
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:54,559
Otherwise,

42
00:02:54,800 --> 00:02:55,559
holding it in is too unbearable.

43
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:57,800
All right.

44
00:02:57,919 --> 00:02:59,000
Don't do this next time.

45
00:03:00,720 --> 00:03:01,720
Tell me, Lin Jiaqi,

46
00:03:02,479 --> 00:03:04,039
when will you like me

47
00:03:04,039 --> 00:03:05,119
as much as I like you?

48
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,279
It seems to me that

49
00:03:07,679 --> 00:03:09,360
you value your work more than me.

50
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:13,440
What are you doing?

51
00:03:15,679 --> 00:03:16,800
We're still at the factory.

52
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,279
I prepared some cash.

53
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:34,360
Use this for now.

54
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:38,479
You're brushing me off with this little money?

55
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:40,639
Do you think I'm a beggar?

56
00:03:40,919 --> 00:03:42,440
Grasp all, lose all.

57
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,080
Be careful, or you won't even get this much.

58
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,360
I'm not blackmailing you.

59
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:47,440
This is what we agreed on before.

60
00:03:47,839 --> 00:03:48,800
Where is my wife's kidney?

61
00:03:49,240 --> 00:03:50,279
What's the rush?

62
00:03:50,679 --> 00:03:51,880
Can this be done in a day or two?

63
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:54,000
If you're so capable,

64
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:54,839
go find it yourself.

65
00:03:55,399 --> 00:03:56,520
You have to give me some time.

66
00:03:56,520 --> 00:03:57,199
Time?

67
00:03:57,520 --> 00:03:59,039
My wife doesn't have time to wait.

68
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:00,919
Her condition has already worsened.

69
00:04:01,639 --> 00:04:02,440
I'm warning you.

70
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,479
I can go to the police station anytime.

71
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:09,160
Don't push your luck.

72
00:04:09,559 --> 00:04:10,600
You want to go to the police station?

73
00:04:10,919 --> 00:04:11,440
Go ahead.

74
00:04:12,039 --> 00:04:13,000
Go see what the result will be.

75
00:04:13,119 --> 00:04:13,960
What will the result be?

76
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:16,119
At worst, I'll take you down with me.

77
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:18,000
Do you really think you can drag me down?

78
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:19,519
Fine.

79
00:04:20,119 --> 00:04:21,079
Just try it.

80
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,480
Threatening me, huh?

81
00:04:23,079 --> 00:04:24,279
See if I dare.

82
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,880
Is it because you got money from me

83
00:04:32,040 --> 00:04:33,119
that you forgot who I am?

84
00:04:33,559 --> 00:04:35,279
If you keep pushing your luck like this,

85
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:37,200
and refuse to back down when given the chance,

86
00:04:37,920 --> 00:04:38,480
I don't know

87
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,799
what I might do myself.

88
00:04:40,679 --> 00:04:42,079
Don't keep testing my bottom line.

89
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:43,480
Understand?

90
00:04:50,040 --> 00:04:51,040
Why is your head so hard?

91
00:04:51,160 --> 00:04:52,200
What do you mean my head is hard?

92
00:04:52,559 --> 00:04:53,720
I'd say you did it on purpose.

93
00:04:57,239 --> 00:04:58,440
You're an old man,

94
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:00,000
why are you in such a hurry?

95
00:05:00,760 --> 00:05:01,519
You bumped me hard.

96
00:05:01,679 --> 00:05:02,760
What do you mean I'm in a hurry?

97
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:04,640
Young people are so reckless.

98
00:05:05,239 --> 00:05:05,920
Seriously.

99
00:05:08,320 --> 00:05:08,920
Are you okay?

100
00:05:09,239 --> 00:05:09,959
I'm fine.

101
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:14,000
By the way,

102
00:05:14,839 --> 00:05:16,359
Jiaqi went back to the city first.

103
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:19,359
She said

104
00:05:19,679 --> 00:05:21,519
there's a special meeting for the secretarial department.

105
00:05:21,959 --> 00:05:22,799
So she left first.

106
00:05:25,399 --> 00:05:26,679
I have a question for you.

107
00:05:26,799 --> 00:05:27,880
I don't know if it's appropriate.

108
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:28,720
Then don't ask.

109
00:05:29,119 --> 00:05:30,000
I don't know if it's appropriate either.

110
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:32,720
Do you like...

111
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:34,279
Why are you so stubborn, old man?

112
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:34,839
I already told you,

113
00:05:34,839 --> 00:05:35,799
don't ask.

114
00:05:35,799 --> 00:05:36,880
I'm not listening, not listening, not listening.

115
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:38,959
Don't be anxious.

116
00:05:39,399 --> 00:05:40,399
Listen to me first.

117
00:05:40,679 --> 00:05:41,320
Do you...

118
00:05:42,079 --> 00:05:43,239
like Jiaqi?

119
00:05:44,399 --> 00:05:45,359
I can feel it.

120
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:47,640
Back then,

121
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,399
when my son looked at Jiaqi,

122
00:05:49,519 --> 00:05:50,519
I had this feeling too.

123
00:05:53,559 --> 00:05:55,079
I do like Lin Jiaqi.

124
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:58,320
I've never hidden that fact.

125
00:06:00,079 --> 00:06:00,720
However,

126
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,799
I've never known

127
00:06:02,799 --> 00:06:04,079
what she thinks in her heart.

128
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,320
That girl Jiaqi,

129
00:06:07,920 --> 00:06:09,320
her standards are just too high.

130
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:10,480
Otherwise, how could she

131
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:11,760
be with my son?

132
00:06:12,399 --> 00:06:14,399
I think your son inherited your genes,

133
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:16,079
which is why he was so stubborn too.

134
00:06:16,359 --> 00:06:17,119
What are you saying?

135
00:06:22,559 --> 00:06:25,000
I don't know if Jiaqi's standards are high,

136
00:06:26,279 --> 00:06:27,559
but the walls around her heart

137
00:06:28,679 --> 00:06:30,000
are built pretty high.

138
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,399
I always feel like I'll never

139
00:06:34,559 --> 00:06:36,119
be able to compete with the person in her heart.

140
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:37,079
Also,

141
00:06:37,559 --> 00:06:38,640
Lin Jiaqi as a person,

142
00:06:38,920 --> 00:06:40,119
her EQ is too low.

143
00:06:40,679 --> 00:06:41,600
I originally thought

144
00:06:41,760 --> 00:06:42,839
I could use this work trip

145
00:06:43,279 --> 00:06:44,720
to go on a date with her or something.

146
00:06:45,239 --> 00:06:46,399
But she left without saying a word.

147
00:06:55,359 --> 00:06:56,440
You're an older man,

148
00:06:56,519 --> 00:06:57,519
why are you living so sloppily?

149
00:06:58,440 --> 00:06:59,600
You didn't even notice your shoelaces are untied.

150
00:07:00,079 --> 00:07:00,959
What if you trip and fall?

151
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:02,720
When you're all alone,

152
00:07:02,799 --> 00:07:04,040
you have to live well.

153
00:07:04,519 --> 00:07:05,359
If you fall down,

154
00:07:05,799 --> 00:07:06,760
I don't have money to compensate you.

155
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,799
Buy three packs of instant noodles and bring them to me right now.

156
00:07:24,279 --> 00:07:26,160
When did you get this?

157
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:27,959
I forgot my phone.

158
00:07:28,279 --> 00:07:29,279
Could I borrow your phone

159
00:07:29,279 --> 00:07:30,000
for a second?

160
00:07:40,920 --> 00:07:42,160
Why are you so slow?

161
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:43,839
I'm starving!

162
00:07:47,480 --> 00:07:49,200
You rush me like there's no tomorrow every day.

163
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,040
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

164
00:07:51,480 --> 00:07:52,119
Wait a minute, slow down.

165
00:07:52,119 --> 00:07:52,640
Hurry up!

166
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:02,480
Oh my god.

167
00:08:06,079 --> 00:08:07,239
Is it your birthday today?

168
00:08:08,119 --> 00:08:08,760
No.

169
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:10,679
Then why is there a cake?

170
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:12,679
Because...

171
00:08:13,359 --> 00:08:15,279
today is a day worth celebrating.

172
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:16,720
What occasion?

173
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:18,839
Please, sit.

174
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:27,839
Blow out the candles.

175
00:08:29,559 --> 00:08:30,519
It's not even my birthday.

176
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:31,720
Why should I blow out the candles?

177
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:32,799
Blow out the candles,

178
00:08:32,799 --> 00:08:33,479
and I'll tell you.

179
00:08:36,359 --> 00:08:36,919
Alright.

180
00:08:38,280 --> 00:08:39,280
You have to close your eyes.

181
00:08:54,039 --> 00:08:55,080
The new product.

182
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:01,799
You're the first one to open it.

183
00:09:10,880 --> 00:09:11,840
It's finally out.

184
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:14,679
Even though

185
00:09:14,919 --> 00:09:17,119
we went through so many twists and turns,

186
00:09:18,119 --> 00:09:19,559
we finally managed to

187
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:20,679
make it happen.

188
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,359
Congratulations, CEO.

189
00:09:29,359 --> 00:09:30,440
Tell me, why is it that

190
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:33,479
in every moment worth celebrating,

191
00:09:34,719 --> 00:09:35,640
I always think of you?

192
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,880
When I wake up every morning,

193
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:40,840
I think of you.

194
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,320
When the warm sunlight

195
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,760
shines on me,

196
00:09:46,039 --> 00:09:47,039
I think of you too.

197
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,159
When I eat something delicious,

198
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,760
or watch a good movie,

199
00:09:53,919 --> 00:09:55,400
or hear a beautiful song...

200
00:09:57,599 --> 00:09:58,760
When I've worked all day

201
00:09:59,000 --> 00:09:59,679
and feel exhausted,

202
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,559
and I come back home,

203
00:10:02,559 --> 00:10:03,440
I always think of you.

204
00:10:07,960 --> 00:10:09,159
I want to share every

205
00:10:09,159 --> 00:10:09,960
beautiful

206
00:10:10,239 --> 00:10:11,440
and memorable moment

207
00:10:12,559 --> 00:10:13,719
with you.

208
00:10:20,799 --> 00:10:21,799
Do you think I'm sick?

209
00:10:24,359 --> 00:10:25,840
Haven't I told you already?

210
00:10:28,760 --> 00:10:29,760
I'm very scared right now.

211
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:33,080
Okay.

212
00:10:34,119 --> 00:10:34,640
I understand.

213
00:10:35,799 --> 00:10:36,599
So,

214
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:37,799
I won't force you

215
00:10:37,799 --> 00:10:38,880
to make any decisions.

216
00:10:39,799 --> 00:10:40,679
I will

217
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,119
stay in a place

218
00:10:43,159 --> 00:10:44,400
where you feel safe,

219
00:10:45,039 --> 00:10:46,239
and just wait for you quietly.

220
00:10:47,599 --> 00:10:48,479
But promise me,

221
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:50,159
you can't run off with someone else.

222
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,159
As long as you know

223
00:10:55,119 --> 00:10:56,440
that to keep you by my side,

224
00:10:57,960 --> 00:10:59,000
I've been trying my best,

225
00:10:59,559 --> 00:11:00,359
that's enough.

226
00:11:10,039 --> 00:11:11,080
I've said so much,

227
00:11:12,159 --> 00:11:13,440
why haven't you said a word?

228
00:11:15,559 --> 00:11:17,159
I think you spoke very well.

229
00:11:18,039 --> 00:11:18,599
That's it?

230
00:11:25,559 --> 00:11:27,520
Do you think I'm being too sentimental?

231
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:30,679
I can't help it.

232
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,520
Ever since I was little,

233
00:11:32,840 --> 00:11:33,719
I've had a great talent for writing

234
00:11:34,280 --> 00:11:35,320
and been very emotional.

235
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:36,960
My essays when I was a kid

236
00:11:37,479 --> 00:11:38,320
always got full marks.

237
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:39,960
The teachers all praised me.

238
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:42,000
It was just unstoppable.

239
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:47,840
Let's go flower viewing next week,

240
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:48,599
okay?

241
00:11:48,599 --> 00:11:49,159
Flower viewing?

242
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:52,799
I remember when I was little,

243
00:11:53,479 --> 00:11:54,919
my parents often took me to see flowers.

244
00:11:56,799 --> 00:11:57,960
Back then, I thought,

245
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,520
if I ever met someone

246
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:01,520
I truly cherished,

247
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,320
I'd go flower viewing with her.

248
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:05,640
And then?

249
00:12:05,960 --> 00:12:06,880
While looking at the flowers,

250
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:08,760
we'd cook instant noodles to eat.

251
00:12:16,719 --> 00:12:18,320
Actually, as long as you're willing to get closer,

252
00:12:19,359 --> 00:12:21,479
even if it's just a little bit,

253
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,359
let the two of us

254
00:12:24,799 --> 00:12:25,479
slowly,

255
00:12:25,880 --> 00:12:27,320
very slowly start,

256
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,039
okay?

257
00:12:40,799 --> 00:12:41,359
Okay.

258
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:44,080
Really.

259
00:12:45,320 --> 00:12:46,599
I was talking about admiring the flowers.

260
00:12:49,599 --> 00:12:50,359
Just now,

261
00:12:50,640 --> 00:12:51,479
didn't you say

262
00:12:51,719 --> 00:12:52,559
you wanted instant noodles?

263
00:12:54,080 --> 00:12:55,359
Instant noodles or cake?

264
00:12:56,039 --> 00:12:56,919
Cake, of course.

265
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:58,119
With such delicious cake,

266
00:12:58,119 --> 00:12:59,080
who would eat instant noodles?

267
00:12:59,159 --> 00:12:59,559
Okay.

268
00:12:59,679 --> 00:13:00,280
I'll cut it.

269
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,159
Where should I start?

270
00:13:14,239 --> 00:13:15,400
How am I supposed to eat the cake now?

271
00:13:15,919 --> 00:13:16,799
Go make me some instant noodles.

272
00:13:24,200 --> 00:13:24,880
Good morning,

273
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:26,440
CEO Gu.

274
00:13:26,640 --> 00:13:27,400
You seem to be in a good mood.

275
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,520
After yesterday's vivid lesson,

276
00:13:31,119 --> 00:13:31,880
Director Feng,

277
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:33,960
do you have any new insights on life?

278
00:13:34,479 --> 00:13:35,440
How could I not?

279
00:13:36,320 --> 00:13:37,359
You made me realize that

280
00:13:37,599 --> 00:13:38,960
when it comes to playing dirty tricks,

281
00:13:39,719 --> 00:13:41,080
how could I ever compare to you, CEO Gu?

282
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:42,479
I will prove to you that

283
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:44,520
no matter in what aspect,

284
00:13:45,200 --> 00:13:47,039
you will always be the loser.

285
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,559
Aren't you just relying on luck?

286
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,320
The reason Aunt Zhang helped you

287
00:13:54,919 --> 00:13:56,039
is all because of your father.

288
00:14:00,239 --> 00:14:01,200
You reap

289
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:03,280
what you sow.

290
00:14:04,039 --> 00:14:05,159
According to what you said,

291
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:07,719
you've ruined so many companies and families before.

292
00:14:11,359 --> 00:14:12,359
I believe

293
00:14:12,679 --> 00:14:13,479
your good luck

294
00:14:13,479 --> 00:14:14,520
will soon hit the limit up.

295
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:16,359
The stock market is just like that.

296
00:14:16,760 --> 00:14:18,080
Then you should be about to take a

297
00:14:18,239 --> 00:14:18,880
nosedive soon.

298
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,760
Do you think I'd be so stupid

299
00:14:21,559 --> 00:14:22,760
as to fall for your trick a second time?

300
00:14:23,039 --> 00:14:24,400
It's too early to say anything now.

301
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:26,719
Who will have the last laugh

302
00:14:26,719 --> 00:14:27,479
is still uncertain.

303
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:29,679
Then please

304
00:14:29,679 --> 00:14:30,559
work hard

305
00:14:31,159 --> 00:14:32,159
and pay back the money quickly.

306
00:14:33,400 --> 00:14:33,919
Excuse me.

307
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:47,679
What are you doing?

308
00:14:50,599 --> 00:14:51,320
It was you.

309
00:14:54,679 --> 00:14:55,880
You killed Du Zheng.

310
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:57,159
What nonsense are you talking about,

311
00:14:58,320 --> 00:14:59,000
Feng Ziang?

312
00:15:00,239 --> 00:15:01,479
You must have been at

313
00:15:01,479 --> 00:15:02,119
the crime scene that day,

314
00:15:03,039 --> 00:15:03,919
together with Du Zheng.

315
00:15:05,400 --> 00:15:06,039
And,

316
00:15:06,599 --> 00:15:07,719
after you hit and killed Du Zheng,

317
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,799
you got out of the car to check, right?

318
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:10,520
Are you crazy?

319
00:15:11,559 --> 00:15:12,440
After what happened yesterday,

320
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,520
you've gotten carried away, haven't you?

321
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,440
This is slander.

322
00:15:15,719 --> 00:15:16,679
You'll be held legally responsible.

323
00:15:17,119 --> 00:15:18,159
After doing such a thing,

324
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:19,799
how do you still have the nerve

325
00:15:19,799 --> 00:15:20,880
to stay by Lin Jiaqi's side?

326
00:15:21,159 --> 00:15:21,679
Gu Tiancheng,

327
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:22,760
I think you're really crazy.

328
00:15:23,359 --> 00:15:23,960
Hurry back to the hospital

329
00:15:24,280 --> 00:15:25,320
and get a proper checkup.

330
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,080
Now that I've caught you today,

331
00:15:36,039 --> 00:15:37,440
I will definitely investigate this matter

332
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,400
to the very end.

333
00:15:40,159 --> 00:15:40,919
Just you wait.

334
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:51,000
Uncle Du

335
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,200
What brings you here?

336
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:55,000
Just here to report on the recent production status.

337
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,039
That makes sense.

338
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,799
The samples for the new products are out now.

339
00:15:58,039 --> 00:15:59,280
So you came over to inspect them.

340
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:01,200
You've seen the samples?

341
00:16:03,559 --> 00:16:04,080
Have a seat.

342
00:16:08,760 --> 00:16:09,320
Yes.

343
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:10,880
Mr. Gu showed them to me.

344
00:16:11,599 --> 00:16:12,320
I see.

345
00:16:13,159 --> 00:16:14,080
I remember

346
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:15,840
when he left the factory,

347
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:16,719
it was already very late.

348
00:16:17,559 --> 00:16:18,479
It was that late,

349
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,520
and he still showed you the samples?

350
00:16:22,119 --> 00:16:23,520
Because it was quite urgent.

351
00:16:24,039 --> 00:16:25,080
Lately, we've been

352
00:16:25,479 --> 00:16:27,039
focusing all our attention on this.

353
00:16:27,239 --> 00:16:28,880
The new product samples are out now,

354
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,239
so

355
00:16:30,239 --> 00:16:31,479
he wanted to share them with someone.

356
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:36,479
Jiaqi,

357
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:38,000
I

358
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:40,280
won't beat around the bush with you.

359
00:16:40,559 --> 00:16:42,080
Can I just ask you a question directly?

360
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:43,559
Go ahead.

361
00:16:44,359 --> 00:16:45,559
In your heart,

362
00:16:46,640 --> 00:16:48,039
do you have feelings for Mr. Gu?

363
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:49,679
It's okay, Jiaqi.

364
00:16:51,039 --> 00:16:52,919
Liking someone isn't a crime.

365
00:16:54,520 --> 00:16:55,239
Uncle Du...

366
00:16:57,280 --> 00:16:58,200
Consider it a plea from me.

367
00:16:59,039 --> 00:16:59,919
Life is so short,

368
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:01,320
and you're so young.

369
00:17:02,799 --> 00:17:04,520
If you always dwell on the past

370
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:06,560
and give up on present opportunities,

371
00:17:08,040 --> 00:17:09,640
when you're as old as I am in the future,

372
00:17:09,920 --> 00:17:11,119
you'll have regrets.

373
00:17:12,199 --> 00:17:14,319
If you like someone, pursue them boldly.

374
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:17,520
Don't have any reservations.

375
00:17:18,680 --> 00:17:19,359
Okay?

376
00:17:19,719 --> 00:17:20,680
Uncle Du...

377
00:17:21,959 --> 00:17:22,640
I'm sorry.

378
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:24,359
I'll just consider it

379
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:25,719
acting on behalf of Du Zheng

380
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,800
to give you away.

381
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:32,880
I know who killed Du Zheng.

382
00:17:33,839 --> 00:17:34,439
Who?

383
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:35,760
Wait a minute.

384
00:17:36,280 --> 00:17:37,599
You'd better calm down first.

385
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:39,400
I know hearing this news

386
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,119
will surprise you.

387
00:17:40,119 --> 00:17:41,119
Stop acting like a wimp.

388
00:17:41,119 --> 00:17:41,839
Just say it.

389
00:17:42,239 --> 00:17:43,359
The murderer who killed Du Zheng

390
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:44,680
is Feng Ziang.

391
00:17:45,479 --> 00:17:46,079
Why?

392
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,439
Do you remember I told you before

393
00:17:48,439 --> 00:17:49,880
that I kept dreaming about that watch?

394
00:17:51,599 --> 00:17:52,640
Today I saw Feng Ziang,

395
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:53,640
and he was wearing that watch.

396
00:17:55,640 --> 00:17:56,839
So you mean to say,

397
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,199
without any reason or logic,

398
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,239
you just dreamed of a watch,

399
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:02,959
and coincidentally, that watch

400
00:18:02,959 --> 00:18:04,079
is the one Feng Ziang wears.

401
00:18:04,079 --> 00:18:04,760
So you concluded

402
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:05,800
that Feng Ziang is the murderer.

403
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:06,280
Right?

404
00:18:07,719 --> 00:18:09,560
Such a sharp-minded good cop.

405
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:10,920
The pride of our nation.

406
00:18:11,160 --> 00:18:12,199
Psycho.

407
00:18:12,199 --> 00:18:13,199
You're seriously sick.

408
00:18:14,359 --> 00:18:15,400
Is being a psycho contagious?

409
00:18:15,719 --> 00:18:16,239
Definitely.

410
00:18:17,040 --> 00:18:18,400
Are you even a police officer?

411
00:18:18,839 --> 00:18:20,079
Do you have any sense of responsibility?

412
00:18:20,319 --> 00:18:21,439
Why don't you go catch the murderer?

413
00:18:22,880 --> 00:18:24,280
If you want me to believe you,

414
00:18:24,719 --> 00:18:26,359
you have to explain clearly

415
00:18:26,359 --> 00:18:27,920
why it's Feng Ziang.

416
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:34,560
What is it?

417
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:36,560
Right here...

418
00:18:37,119 --> 00:18:37,800
is Du Zheng.

419
00:18:39,959 --> 00:18:40,719
Are you crazy?

420
00:18:41,719 --> 00:18:42,839
Why don't you take him to see a doctor?

421
00:18:43,400 --> 00:18:44,040
Lin Yaoyao.

422
00:18:45,680 --> 00:18:46,880
I'm certain Feng Ziang

423
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:47,680
was at the crime scene.

424
00:18:48,199 --> 00:18:48,959
And I'm sure

425
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,040
he even got out of the car to check

426
00:18:51,040 --> 00:18:52,359
if Du Zheng was dead or alive.

427
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:53,479
Also,

428
00:18:54,239 --> 00:18:55,280
regarding the substandard materials incident,

429
00:18:55,839 --> 00:18:56,800
Feng Ziang is the real culprit.

430
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:58,400
Why?

431
00:18:59,439 --> 00:19:00,359
How do you know?

432
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:03,959
Anyway, there are still many

433
00:19:03,959 --> 00:19:05,079
complicated reasons right now.

434
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:07,280
I can't tell you.

435
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,000
But please believe me.

436
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,119
I'm begging you, okay?

437
00:19:13,359 --> 00:19:14,319
Look into him again.

438
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:18,560
Hello.

439
00:19:18,959 --> 00:19:20,400
I want to report something.

440
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:21,719
There's this guy.

441
00:19:22,359 --> 00:19:23,880
After getting a heart transplant,

442
00:19:24,119 --> 00:19:24,800
he secretly accessed

443
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:26,079
the donor's medical information.

444
00:19:26,520 --> 00:19:27,319
I suspect him of

445
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:29,319
illegal organ trafficking.

446
00:19:42,640 --> 00:19:43,560
So early.

447
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,280
Couldn't wait to see me?

448
00:19:47,640 --> 00:19:48,920
Hello, is this Gu Tiancheng?

449
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:51,359
Yes, speaking.

450
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:52,239
What's wrong?

451
00:19:53,079 --> 00:19:54,319
Please come with us.

452
00:20:15,280 --> 00:20:16,359
I know you don't want to see me.

453
00:20:17,239 --> 00:20:18,359
And I don't want to upset you either.

454
00:20:19,959 --> 00:20:21,280
But as a former friend,

455
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:22,959
there are things I must warn you about.

456
00:20:23,439 --> 00:20:24,439
I don't think there's anything left

457
00:20:25,119 --> 00:20:26,280
for us to talk about.

458
00:20:26,640 --> 00:20:27,599
I feel it's necessary

459
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:29,599
when you're being deceived

460
00:20:29,599 --> 00:20:30,520
to step up and warn you.

461
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:32,119
What exactly are you trying to say?

462
00:20:32,560 --> 00:20:34,040
Have you fallen for Gu Tiancheng?

463
00:20:35,479 --> 00:20:36,719
That's my personal business.

464
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:38,479
I don't need to tell you.

465
00:20:38,640 --> 00:20:39,439
I guessed right.

466
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:41,839
So you do like him.

467
00:20:43,800 --> 00:20:44,880
If you came here

468
00:20:45,439 --> 00:20:46,680
just to ask me this,

469
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,400
then we have nothing more to say.

470
00:20:49,640 --> 00:20:50,439
Who you like

471
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:51,800
is up to you.

472
00:20:52,239 --> 00:20:53,239
I have no right to interfere.

473
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:56,040
But between Du Zheng and this Gu Tiancheng...

474
00:20:56,040 --> 00:20:57,479
Du Zheng will always be in my heart.

475
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:01,800
Have you ever thought about

476
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:03,439
why you fell for Gu Tiancheng?
